Colouration in preservative. After one year of preservation in 4 % formaldehyde solution, male colouration was yellow to light brown (similar to live colouration of females), and the pelvic part whitish (
Fig. 1 A
). Black marking is present on the opercular region, gill membrane and distal part of dorsal fin of some individuals (including the holotype ). Small black dots are present on the caudal and dorsal fins. The anal, pelvic and pectoral fins are orange. Female body colouration is identical and fins are transparent. Rarely, the black dots are visible.

Etymology. The species is named in honour of the late Jaroslav Kadlec (
1951–2006
) from Brno, Czech Republic , a renowned killifish breeder recognized worldwide for his articles on killifish breeding, ecology, and his photographs. To be pronounced “khadlatsi”.

