In conclusion,
N. kadleci
may be a short-lived rather than rare species and occurs in a range of small temporary pools between the Save and Zambezi River. It is expected that it might play an important role in the comparative research on aging where
N. furzeri
(from drier regions than
N. kadleci
) is becoming a model species due to its short lifespan (
Valdesalici & Cellerino 2003
;
Genade et al. 2005
;
Terzibasi et al. 2007
;
Terzibasi et al. 2008
)
